 \int_a^\infty \frac{1}{x^2+1}dx, a>0 
x = \tan(t)
dx = \sec^2(t) \, dt
\tan^2(t) + 1 = \sec^2(t)
I = \int_a^\infty \dfrac{dx}{x^2+1}
I = \int_{\arctan(a)}^{\pi/2} \, dt = \dfrac{\pi}2 - \arctan(a) = \text{arccot}(a)
 \int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{1+x^2}dx=\frac{\pi}{2}-\tan^{-1}a. 
 \int_a^\infty \frac{1}{x^2+1}dx=\tan^{-1}x\mid_{a}^\infty =\frac{\pi}2-\tan^{-1}a=\cot^{-1}a
x=\tan\theta
\tan^{-1}x
\tan^{-1}b-\tan^{-1}a
b\to\infty
